      "content": "If you feel okay and there's no fever, you can certainly manage this with some basic home care. Apply a thin layer of Neosporin, keep it covered with a clean bandage, and keep the area clean. However, if you see any spreading redness, increasing pain, or pus, you need to stop and get immediate attention, even if it means finding an emergency clinic. Trust your instincts, but don't let minor concerns turn into a major problem by ignoring clear signs of trouble.",
